#Tukey Test: (lm is for linear regression model, aov is for anova)

hot_lm <- (ig_h$integument_color ~ ig_h$date)#for Integument Color Across Treatments Over Time
hot_aov = aov(hot_lm)
summary(hot_aov)
##             Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)  
## ig_h$date    5  5.477  1.0954   3.085  0.014 *
## Residuals   73 25.922  0.3551                 
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
hot_tukey <- TukeyHSD(x=hot_aov)

dat_all <- crab_dat %>%
  mutate(day = recode(date, "7/8/2022" = 4, "7/12/2022" = 8, "7/15/2022" = 11, "7/19/2022" = 15, "7/22/2022" = 18, "7/26/2022" = 22)) %>%
  mutate(temperature = recode(treatment.tank, "1" = 14, "2" = 6, "3" = 31, "4" = 14, "5" = 6, "6" = 31)) %>% mutate(sex = recode(sex, "F"=1, "M"=2)) %>%
  select(., -c(treatment.tank, date)) #Make recode dates to days and create a new column for temperature. Drop date and treatment.tank
